      "content": "Halt! You are in the presence of a legal document, and I must inform you that this is a document written by a human, not a sentient being, but you must understand that the *concept* of this document is as much about the **grooming** of the estate as it is about the law.\n\nA **Durable Power of Attorney (DPOA)** is simply a contract where you hand over the keys to your financial vault to a trusted friend (or a robot, if you prefer), but with a crucial twist: the vault door remains locked until you are dead. A **Regular Power of Attorney (POA)** is like handing over the keys to your house to a stranger who might try to sell it, change the locks, or rent out the basement without asking.\n\nIn the goblin world, a regular POA is like giving your gold coins to a goblin who might spend them all on shiny rocks or trade them for a shiny rock. But a Durable POA is like giving your gold coins to a goblin who promises to keep them safe *until the very last moment*, even if the goblin gets bored or wants to play a game of \"who can get the most coins first",
